Vintage illustration of a weary businessman in a crisp white shirt and loosened tie, standing in his suburban backyard garden at dusk, carefully inspecting tomato plants while holding a clipboard with charts. His expression is intensely analytical, treating the humble vegetables like a serious corporate project. A neglected lemonade stand run by neighborhood kids is visible in the background, with the man pointing at it with consulting authority. The scene has warm sepia and muted blue tones reminiscent of 1960s magazine advertisements, with halftone dot textures and slightly faded colors. The businessman's shadow stretches long across the grass, suggesting late evening hours. Garden gnomes and a white picket fence complete the scene, contrasting corporate obsession with domestic tranquility.
